JENKINS AUTOMATION — MAVEN JAVA & WEB PROJECTS

https://github.com/HARIVIGNESHRAO/SELAB.git (maven java and web week8)
Steps for MavenJava Automation
Step 1: Open Jenkins → New Item
Step 2: Create Freestyle Project (MavenJava_Build)
• Enter name → OK
• Description → Java Build demo
• SCM → Git repo URL
• Branches → /main or /master
Build Steps:
• Add: Invoke top-level Maven targets → Goals: clean
• Add: Invoke top-level Maven targets → Goals: install
Post-build Actions:
• Archive the artifacts → Files to archive: //
• Build other projects → Projects to build: MavenJava_Test (Trigger: Only if build is stable)
Step 3: Create MavenJava_Test
• Enter name → OK
• Description → Test demo
• Build Environment → Check: Delete the workspace before build starts
• Copy artifacts from another project → Project: MavenJava_Build (Build: Stable build only)
• Artifacts to copy → //
• Add: Invoke top-level Maven targets → Goals: test
• Post-build: Archive the artifacts → Files to archive: //*
Step 4: Create Pipeline View
• Click “+” beside All on dashboard → Enter name: MavenJava_Pipeline → Select Build pipeline view → Create
• Pipeline Initial job: MavenJava_Build
Step 5: Run the Pipeline
• Click the pipeline trigger / run
• Open the small black box → check console output
• Success = pipeline turns green and MavenJava_Test should be triggered and pass

Maven Web Automation Steps
Step 1: Click New Item → Create Freestyle Project (MavenWeb_Build)
• Enter name → OK
• Description → Web Build demo
• SCM → Git repo URL
• Branches → /main or /master
Build Steps:
• Add: Invoke top-level Maven targets → Goals: clean
• Add: Invoke top-level Maven targets → Goals: install
Post-build Actions:
• Archive the artifacts → Files to archive: //
• Build other projects → Projects to build: MavenWeb_Test (Trigger: Only if build is stable)
Step 3: Create MavenWeb_Test
• Enter name → OK
• Description → Test demo
• Build Environment → Check: Delete the workspace before build starts
• Copy artifacts from another project → Project: MavenWeb_Build (Build: Stable only)
• Artifacts to copy → //
• Add: Invoke top-level Maven targets → Goals: test
• Post-build: Archive artifacts → Files to archive: //*
• Post-build: Build other projects → Projects to build: MavenWeb_Deploy
Step 4: Create MavenWeb_Deploy
• Enter name → OK
• Description → Web Code Deployment
• Build Environment → Check: Delete the workspace before build starts
• Copy artifacts from another project → Project: MavenWeb_Test (Build: Stable only)
• Artifacts to copy → //*
Post-build Actions:
• Deploy WAR/EAR to a container

WAR/EAR File: //.war*

Context path: Webpath

Add container → Tomcat 9.x remote

Credentials → Username: admin, Password: 1234

Tomcat URL → https://localhost:8085/

Step 5: Create MavenWeb Pipeline View
• Click “+” beside All → Enter name: MavenWeb_Pipeline → Select Build pipeline view
• Initial job: MavenWeb_Build
Step 6: Run Pipeline & Check Output
• Click RUN on the pipeline view
• Click the small black box → open console to verify build logs
• If green → builds succeeded
• Open Tomcat manager → click /webpath → provide Tomcat credentials (admin/1234) → view deployed app output
